Key Match Events: Dorian Finney-Smith hit a game-winning three-pointer with 1:13 left in the fourth quarter.
Dennis Schroder drove past Edey and made a layup to extend the lead to 106-101 with 32 seconds remaining.
Ja Morant drove and spun mid-air for a layup late in the second quarter, wowing the crowd.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Memphis Grizzlies rookie Alex Edey had season highs of 25 points and 11 rebounds.
The game marked the Nets' first time playing at Barclays Center since the 2021-22 season.
